center
tikzpicture[scale=0.4]
 % Wall
 ll[gray!20] (0,0) rectangle (-0.5,9);
 (0,0) ŌĆō (0,9);

 % Ground
 (-0.5,0) ŌĆō (7,0);

 % Ladder
 (6,0) ŌĆō (0,8);

 % Right angle
 (0,0.5) ŌĆō (0.5,0.5) ŌĆō (0.5,0);

 % Labels
 at (3,0) {6 ft};
 at (0,4) {$h$};
 at (3,4.5) {10 ft};
tikzpicture
center

The wall, ground, and ladder form a right triangle with the ladder as 
hypotenuse:
$$
6^2 + h^2 &= 10^2 \\
36 + h^2 &= 100 \\
h^2 &= 64 \\
h &= 8
$$

The ladder reaches 8 feet up the wall.

The horizontal distance is $|7 - 1| = 6$ and the vertical distance 
is $|10 - 2| = 8$. These form the legs of a right triangle with the 
distance $d$ as hypotenuse:

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.4]
 (0,0) ŌĆō (9,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,0) ŌĆō (0,11) node[above] {$y$};

 ll[AtlasTeal] (1,2) circle (4pt) node[below left] {$A(1,2)$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (7,10) circle (4pt) node[above right] {$B(7,10)$};

 (1,2) ŌĆō (7,10);
 (1,2) ŌĆō (7,2) ŌĆō (7,10);

 at (4,2) {6};
 at (7,6) {8};
 at (4,6) {$d$};
tikzpicture
center

\[
d = \sqrt{6^2 + 8^2} = \sqrt{36 + 64} = \sqrt{100} = 10
\]

The distance is 10 units.
